# Cursor IDE default model and mode (local preferences)

## New Agent windows (workspace habit)

**Load Composer 2 (Fast) first** whenever you open a **new** Agent (or Composer) panel, before the first substantive prompt or heavy tool use:

1. Open the **model picker** on the Agent/Composer input.
2. Choose **Composer 2 (Fast)** (not a different default the UI may show on a fresh window).

Also set **Cursor Settings → Models** so **Composer 2 (Fast)** is your default where the product exposes that option—fewer surprises when a new chat opens.

If a task explicitly needs another model (e.g. a named “max” or reasoning model), switch after the first message; the standing preference is still **Composer 2 (Fast) first**.

## What repo rules cannot do

**`.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files do not set** which model Cursor runs for Composer, Agent, or Chat. They only shape instructions for a session after the product has already chosen a model.

Do not tell users that a rule can “force” Composer 2 Fast or a default Agent session—that is **editor state**, not Git-tracked config. This file documents **operator habit + IDE settings**, not enforcement.

## Preferred IDE defaults (operator convention)

- **Composer / Agent model:** **Composer 2 (Fast)** — set via **Cursor Settings → Models** or the **model picker** in the Agent/Composer input. The choice persists until changed.
- **Internal model id** (for debugging or support): often stored as `composer-2-fast` in local app storage alongside `aiSettings.modelConfig.composer`; exact storage may change with Cursor versions.
- **New chat mode:** If new sessions open in the wrong mode (e.g. Ask vs Agent), check settings for **default mode** / **remember last mode**. Some builds persist **`defaultMode2`: `"last"`** behavior (new chats follow the last-used mode). Prefer **Agent** when you want every new Agent session to start in Agent mode, if the UI offers that.

## CLI vs IDE

- **Cursor IDE** (panels, Composer, Agent): defaults are **local** to the install (not synced via this repo).
- **Cursor Agent CLI:** model selection is separate; see [CLI configuration](https://cursor.com/docs/cli/reference/configuration) and `/model` in the CLI.

## When to mention this in chat

If someone asks how to make **every new** Composer/Agent use Composer 2 Fast: point them to **Cursor Settings → Models** and **default mode** options, not to a new `.mdc` rule as a substitute.
